page.title: 09PLANTLIFE:WALK AROUND NATEBY
page.content: A WALK AROUND NATEBY ON 27TH JULY 1985 HEDGES OF HAWTHORN, WITH WILD GOOSE- BERRY AND ELDERFLOWER BUSHES. OCCA- SIONAL TREES OF BEECH, SYCAMORE AND OAK.COLOUR ALONG THE WAY - BRIGHT BLUE MEADOW CRANESBILL,YELLOW HEDGE BED- STRAW,BUTTERCUP AND NIPPLEWORT,WHITE OXEYE DAISY AND THE RED HEMP NETTLE. TINY WILD STRAWBERRIES CAN BE SEEN AND TO CONTRAST THE GIANT PALE PURPLE BELLFLOWER.THE COMMONER PLANTS: COW PARSLEY, NETTLES,GOOSEGRASS,COCKSFOOT, MEADOW FOXTAIL AND THE MEADOW AND RYE- GRASSES ALL FLOURISH.INTO NATEBY AND THERE IS A SMALL BECK WHICH RUNS ALONG THE BOTTOM OF THE VILLAGE. IN IT IS A WEALTH OF PLANTLIFE - OUTSTANDING IS MONKEY MUSK, A BEAUTIFUL YELLOW AND RED FLOWER.THE WATER SUPPORTS MEADOW- SWEET, WATER FORGET-ME-NOT, FOOLS WATERCRESS AND THE PURPLE LESSER KNAP- WEED.
